:::summary
Mathematics is the science of pattern, structure, quantity, and logical deduction. From counting sheep to modeling the quantum behavior of particles, mathematics is the universal language of precision and rigorous reasoning. It is humanity's most successful tool for understanding the physical world — and, many argue, a window into truths that are eternal, necessary, and beautiful.
:::

